# HW-016d -- ES8311 on-board analog mic capture HW-VERIFIED WORKING (issue #6)

Date: 2026-06-06
Board: m5stack_sticks3/esp32s3/procpu  (M5StickS3, ESP32-S3-PICO-1-N8R8)
Build: demo (overlay-ble + overlay-audio + overlay-ir), CONFIG_APP_AUDIO
Firmware: a live-capture diagnostic (audio_mic_monitor) -- full-duplex I2S
          (I2S_DIR_BOTH), speaker amp OFF, NO beep. TX streams silence to keep
          the shared BCLK/WS running; each window reports the MAX rms/peak over
          ~16 captured RX blocks of the ES8311 ADC (slot 0).

Method / stimulus: with the device quiet the capture sits at the noise floor
(rms ~0-6, then ~70-100 as room ambience). Then LOUD external sounds (hand
claps / speech close to the on-board mic) were made. The captured RMS jumps to
the tens-of-thousands with the peak pinning at the 16-bit full scale (32767).

Conclusion: the full analog capture chain -- on-board MEMS mic (MSM381A3729H9BPC)
-> ES8311 MIC1 differential ADC -> SoC I2S0 RX (DIN G16) -> capture DSP -- works
and digitizes real acoustic audio. The earlier HW-016/AUD-H2 "rms=0 during the
beep" reading was a WEAK-ACOUSTIC-STIMULUS confound: the tiny on-board speaker at
the codec's low playback volume barely couples to the adjacent mic, so a
beep-only test reads the noise floor regardless of mic health. It was never an
analog/ADC fault -- the `0x44=0x68` digital-mux loopback (rms=4089/peak=5800,
2026-06-05) had already proven ASDOUT + I2S0 RX + DSP, and every ADC register
reads back exactly as written. Issue #6 RESOLVED; PAGE_AUDIO is now a live
mic-level meter (audio_mic_sample()).

